snippet.textDisplay: Driver came across as really uptight and borderline up himself. Whether I'm right or wrong is beside the point, that's just how he seemed, to me. He barely engaged, even on a body language level. Did he even smile once? Articulate, and a couple of insightful comments, but emotionally, nothing. Maybe it's a marine thing. Loved him in Marriage Story, btw, although the character now appears quite similar to him, so possibly not a great stretch, thespian-wise. For me, a good character requires more than a script, or navigating the treacherous waters of collaboration, it's the idiosyncrasies, the details between the lines, that separates a great performance from a good one.
